<L>__{exterior loch muick day}
<A>__{the next day. brown is rowing victoria across the loch. the equerries wait on the shore. victoria trails her hand in the water, frowning at the surface. brown concentrates on the oars, slipping them carefully through the water.}
<C>__{victoria}
<D>__{i received a letter today from mr disraeli. parliament is calling for my return to public duties.}
<P>__{(beat)}
<D>__{why won't they let us be?}
<A>__{brown does not answer.}
<C>__{victoria }
<D>__{he insists that the country expects me to preside over the opening of the new session. i refuse to offer sustenance to enable his weakening grip. besides, you know how much i should hate it. it frightens me.}
<A>__{she notices that brown has said nothing.}
<C>__{victoria }
<D>__{john?}
<A>__{brown does not look at her. finally:}
<C>__{brown}
<D>__{we can't always have what we wish.}
<A>__{victoria stares at him.}
